comments.body: [~kedwards], check to see what could be done for 3.4.  The issue is it takes a few hours to sync large #'s of users

There are currently (during 3.4 development) performance issues with both euare-* commands and the admin UI with "large" numbers (1000s) of accounts. For example, with 3000 accounts it takes ~15 seconds to list accounts as the cloud admin ("euare-accountlist") and ~30 seconds to view any of the "Identity Management" screens in the admin UI. The "Identity Management" section consists of:

* Accounts
* Groups
* Users
* Policies
* Keys
* Certificates

It looks possible to largely address the performance issue for 10,000s of accounts without database or architectural changes, though 100,000s of accounts would probably be at the limit of usability. The fix would be to avoid performing work for each account individually when looking up data and when performing authorization checks. There would not be changes to the admin UI client (GWT) or the API used by that client. There would be changes to the auth package (Accounts, etc)

To fix all of the above areas would require ~1 day of development and would require some QA effort for both euare-* and the admin UI (though it looks like euare-* changes would be smaller than the admin UI changes)

There is some risk of scope creep, fixing the main listings in the admin UI sections could reveal other issues, though this was not the case for the account or group sections.

I did some further testing with a small number of accounts but 1000 users to determine the current performance.

Using euare commands to list users as admin of a non-eucalyptus account takes ~40 seconds, for other users in the account listing takes ~1.75 minutes. Note that the default client timeout is 30 seconds so you have to adjust the configuration accordingly.

In the admin UI, viewing the user listing takes ~1 minute as admin of a non-eucalyptus account and ~3.5 minutes for other users in the account.

It looks like you can use multiples of these results as a fairly accurate guide to timings with more or less users, e.g. with 2000 users the user listing in the admin UI takes ~2 minutes as admin of a non-eucalyptus account (or ~30 seconds with 500 users)

[~sjones], quick question, was there a reason to use EntityWrapper vs Entities with in the following method : DatabaseAuthProvider class methods : listUsersForAccounts() and listGroupsForAccounts() and listPoliciesForUsers() and listAccessKeysForUsers() and listAccountsByStatus() .Thanks.
[~kedwards], the reason is consistent behaviour with the rest of Euare. If we want to switch to Entities I think we should do so throughout the module.
[~sjones], thanks for the explanation.  Is now the time to purge the Euare service of the EntityWrapper class?
[~spark], would you please review [~sjones]'s suggested fix.  I took a look at the code, seems sound to me.

The admin UI performance issue is not fully addressed as performance is poor with ~100,000 accounts/users, but you should now see pages rendering in under a minute (previously it would take hours).

Using the admin UI search facilities now provides reasonable performance:

http://www.eucalyptus.com/docs/eucalyptus/3.4/index.html#admin-guide/dashboard_search.html

Fix Verified

Using the lic file provided it takes just a second for users/accounts to show up in the admin console and when switching between different pages of results.
